name: **Stack of Beans**
description: Stack of Beans W228-314 Sheet 89 1km WSW of the headland on the W side of Glandore Harbour, and 1km E of Squince Harbour lies a group of islands the smallest of which is this stack. Named for its parabolic appearance viewed from the N, it looks like y=x2 inverted. Landing is usually easy on the N side and climbing to the top is safe and handy. The views W take the breath away.
